<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="674" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 664.119/355</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 3461</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-10">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1918</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 27.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to this Legation’s
                                telegram No. 3224 of May 2, 1918 (Mr. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DEL1">Dresel</persName>’s No. 21),
                                concerning the new lumber convention between the Allied Governments
                                and the Swiss Government,<note n="1" xml:id="d674fn1">Not
                                    printed.</note> I have the honor to transmit herewith copy and
                                translation of an official communication from the Swiss Department
                                of Public Economy, stating that the Federal Council has ratified
                                this convention as concluded on May 1, 1918.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pleasant A. Stovall</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                            <pb facs="0798" n="1632" xml:id="pg_1632"/>
                            <frus:attachment>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#center">[Enclosure—Translation]</seg>
                                </opener>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Swiss Department of
                                            Public Economy</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                            Legation</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 6349</seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-07">
                                            <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>The Swiss Department of Public Economy has the honor to bring to
                                    the knowledge of the Legation of the United States of America
                                    that the Federal Council has ratified the convention relative to
                                    lumber, as well as the minutes of the last conference, concluded
                                    on May 1, 1918, between the delegates of the Allied Governments
                                    and those of the Federal Government.</p>
                                <p>The Department avails itself of this occasion to renew to the
                                    Legation of the United States of America the assurance of its
                                    high esteem.</p>
                            </frus:attachment>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>